        <body>
            <div xml:id="d.1">
                <head type="title">Miklós Oláh to a Provost called Joannes (Binche, 12 October
                    1532)</head>
                <floatingText type="regesta">
                    <body>
                        <p xml:id="reg.p.1">What he had always feared has happened, that is, the
                            destruction has reached Hungary. Péter Perényi was captured, and the
                            news came, he does not know whether to believe it, that King John I was
                            also captured by the Turks. This unfortunate fate is awaiting the rest
                            of the Hungarians as well, namely if the Turks conquer Hungary and
                            capture the nobility and divide up the country, the nobility will have
                            no name any more either, and eternal servitude awaits them. Their only
                            cure is if King Ferdinand I comes to Hungary and recaptures the
                            castles.</p>
                    </body>
                </floatingText>
                <pb facs="15321012_1_1.jpg"/>
                <p xml:id="p.1">Ad Ioannem praepositum.<note type="critic" xml:id="note.1">We do not
                        know him more closely, see Ep. 172, Ep. 264, Ep. 265, and Ep.
                            269.<ref>olahus.tei.15320913_1</ref></note><ref>/o:olahus.tei.15320913_1</ref><ref>/o:olahus.tei.15320913_2</ref><ref>/o:olahus.tei.15320917_1</ref></p>
                <p xml:id="p.2">Quod semper veritus sum, nunc evenisse videtur, nostros scilicet </p>
                <pb facs="15321012_1_2.jpg"/>
                <p xml:id="p.3">Hungaros in magnam perniciem venturos. <persName>Petrus
                        Perenny</persName><note type="critic" xml:id="note.2">Péter Perényi was
                        caught and kidnapped in the summer of 1532, see <hi rend="smallcap"
                            >Puskár</hi> 2008, 303.</note> iampridem a Turca in miseram abductus est
                    captivitatem, sicuti hac de re diu ad te scripsi.<note type="critic"
                        xml:id="note.3">This letter is not extant.</note> Nunc venit fama, nescio,
                    an vera, Turcam eundem ipsum <persName>Ioannem</persName> quoque vaivodam
                    cepisse, non ipsius parcens infirmitati quo <choice>
                        <orig>extrenue</orig>
                        <supplied>extreme</supplied>
                    </choice> nunc <choice>
                        <orig>labore</orig>
                        <supplied>laborare</supplied>
                    </choice> dicitur, et <placeName>Constantinopolim</placeName> duxisse.
                    Infelicissimus is exitus alios etiam Hungaros manebit. <choice>
                        <orig>Nan</orig>
                        <supplied>Nam</supplied>
                    </choice> si Turca totam suae ditioni subegerit
                        <placeName>Hungariam</placeName><del corresp="editor">Hungariam</del>, omnes
                    etiam reliquos dominos et potiores nobiles abducet,
                        <placeName>Hungariam</placeName>que ipsam suis distribuet officialibus et
                    conservandam et regendam; nec erit ullum nobilitatis <del corresp="Olahus"
                        >futuram</del><add corresp="Olahus" type="corr">futurae</add> in
                        <placeName>Hungaria</placeName> nomen; sed <choice>
                        <orig>perpetuum</orig>
                        <supplied>perpetuam</supplied>
                    </choice> et domini et nobiles <del corresp="editor">fuerunt</del> servient
                    servitutem, aut mortem patientur crudelissimam. Unum videtur esse hoc remedium <choice>
                        <orig>huiuc</orig>
                        <supplied>huius</supplied>
                    </choice> malo avertendo: si rex noster <persName>Ferdinandus</persName>, ut iam
                    coepisse dicitur, cum exercitu ad <placeName>Hungariam</placeName> descenderit,
                    et castra finitima, quae Turcae iampridem nostra aetate occuparant, rursus
                    recuperaverit. Nam si id non fiet, numquam firmum in
                        <placeName>Hungaria</placeName> habere poterit imperium. Turcis libere
                    semper, dum voluerint, eam et invadentibus et depraedantibus. Si tu rebus
                    nostris ita stantibus aliquid nobis afferre consilii poteris, cura id facere.
                    Vale.</p>
                <p xml:id="p.4"><placeName>Binsii</placeName> 12. Octobris 1532.</p>
            </div>
